The Police in Osun  on Monday arraigned a 45-year – old man , Yusuf Murtala , before an Osogbo Chief Magistrates’ Court over  alleged dangerous driving. Murtala, who  was arraigned on a five – count charge, however,  pleaded not guilty. The prosecutor, Insp Jacob Akintunde, told the court that the defendant committed the offences on March 15, at about 8:10.a.m. , along Oke-fia Rounderabout in Osogbo. HOW NIGERIAN MEN CAN NOW NATURALLY STOP PREMATURE EJACULATION, LOW SPERM COUNT AND OTHER MEN'S SEXUAL NEEDS. MADAM ALWAYS WANTS IT BIGGER, STRONGER AND LONG-LASTING!!! Akintunde said that Murtala drove a mini bus with registration number Osun KNR 955 XA in a dangerous manner without any road safety consciousness. He said that the defendant had no driving licence , no vehicle licence, no insurance certificate , hackney stage carrier , and Road Worthiness, when he was arrested by the police . Data Protection: NITDA Fines Electronics Coy N5m For Data Breach – Official Tencent Loses $62bn, Wiping Out Value Of Fintech Business The prosecutor said the offences contravened Sections 7, 21 (b) , 142 and 139 of the Road Traffic Act (RTA) of the Laws of Nigeria , 2015 and Vol. 6, Cap 146 Laws of Osun , 2002. The defence counsel , Mr Joseph Babalola , prayed the court to grant his client bail in the most liberal terms. The magistrate , Mr O.A. Oloyade, however , found the defendant guilty of the offences committed and ordered that the defendant shoul pay the sum of N2,500 as fine on each charge. (NAN )